<item>
            <title>[LU-3568] Leading comments should be stripped from commit messages</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3568</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Sometimes, git likes to insert &quot;git status&quot; commentary at the top of an auto-generated commit message starter file.  If the committer carelessly neglects to remove the stuff, the script thinks the message has a missing commit summary line.  The fix is trivial.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
